This paper is primarily focused on wireless networks and their optimization, which falls under the category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of linear programming and optimization techniques, which falls under Information Theory (cs.IT) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Cloud RAN (C-RAN) stations, which falls under Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) as C-RANs often use machine learning algorithms for optimization.
